<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="86.[192,1440,675,763]" pageId="86" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,675,699]" pageId="86" pageNumber="85">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is not an easily distinguished species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[884,982,675,699]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Prodilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[884,982,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="85">Prodilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the entirely dark brown elytron, closely spaced dorsal punctures, basally emarginate prosternum, and long basal lobe of male genitalia will aid in identification.
</paragraph>
